TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bird, Andrew
AU  - Du, Ding
AU  - Karolyi, Stephen A
T1  - Cross-Market Effects of Consolidation: Evidence from Banking
PY  - 2024
Y1  - 2024/11/01
DO  - 10.1093/rcfs/cfae012
JO  - The Review of Corporate Finance Studies
JA  - Review of Corporate Finance Studies
VL  - 13
IS  - 4
SP  - 999
EP  - 1029
SN  - 2046-9128
AB  - The U.S. banking sector had nearly 70% fewer banks in 2022 relative to 1989, primarily because of mergers. We develop a methodology to estimate cross-market spillover effects of bank mergers and test whether the operations of incumbents facing consolidating competitors in one market are affected in other markets. We find that nonmerging banks within a market that are one standard deviation more exposed to mergers in other markets increase deposits by 2.1% relative to their less exposed competitors. Our methodology may be applied elsewhere to assess the aggregate impacts of industry consolidation and illustrates challenges with product-based or geographic market definitions.
Y2  - 4/24/2026
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rcfs/cfae012
ER  - 




